news.title: Barratt's pre-tax profit rises 0.6% to $586.30 million
news.para: Barratt Chief Executive Officer David Thomas said that increased levels of household savings during the pandemic had helped consumers reassess their options, leading to higher transaction levels, and purchasing power has stayed strong.

news.title: Property ladder too high for central Europe's first-time buyers
news.para: The Czech Republic ranks as the least affordable housing market in Europe with an average of 12.2 gross annual salaries needed to buy a 70-square-metre apartment, according to Deloitte's housing affordability survey released in 2021.

news.title: Gurugram civic body probe five years after road built on HSVP plots
news.para: A three-member committee has been constituted by MCG to find out how a road was constructed over HSVP plots in Sector 49. The road in question has affected at least eight plots of the HSVP, the market price of which is around Rs 24 crore.

news.title: ACC bags Kannur Limestone Block in Karnataka
news.para: ACC, a subsidiary of Swiss building material major Holcim group (earlier LafargeHolcim), had participated in an e-auction of the block, located in Kalburgi district of Karnataka.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace to buy 9.24 acres land in Mumbai from M&M for Rs 365 crore
news.para: This new project will be Mahindra Lifespace's second residential development in Kandivali after its successful 'Mahindra Roots' project and will offer about 1 million square feet of carpet area.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body gives more time to 80 households to drain waste water into sewage
news.para: The municipal corporation (MC) has recently disconnected 12 connections, following which many people shifted their connections. For the few remaining, the MC has given time till February end to shift their connections.

news.title: SC allows ED to rely on forensic auditors' report for charge sheet against Unitech ex-promoters
news.para: Additional Solicitor General Madhavi Divan, appearing for the ED, submitted that the agency is going to file the charge sheet next week in the money laundering case lodged the Chandras.

news.title: Streetlights for villages in Vadodara civic body limits
news.para: The VMC had decided to provide streetlights in these areas as lights like filament bulbs, tube lights, sodium lights and others were still being used in these areas that were earlier governed by gram panchayats.

news.title: RBI keeps benchmark lending rate unchanged at 4%
news.para: RBI Governor Shaktikanta Das said the monetary policy committee decided to hold the lending rate, or the repo rate, steady at 4 per cent, and its reverse repo, or the rate at which it absorbs excess cash from lenders - unchanged at 3.35 per cent.

news.title: No hike in property tax in Pune civic body limits
news.para: The standing committee of the PMC on Wednesday decided not to increase the property and entertainment tax for the 2022-23 fiscal.

news.title: Vijayawada: 'Walk to work' boon awaits colony residents
news.para: Krishna district administration developed layouts at Nunna, Surampalli, Kondapavuluru, Velagaleru and other villages near Vijayawada and allocated plots to the beneficiaries.

news.title: Telangana: Rs 5,000 penalty on five civic officials over building permits
news.para: The highest number of applications 19 are pending with Mani Bushan for the past 19 working days. “This is a gross violation of the mandate of the government’s TSbPASS Act.

news.title: Berger Paints' net profit falls 8% to Rs 253 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Its revenue from operations during October-December 2021 jumped 20.42 per cent to Rs 2,550.77 crore, compared with Rs 2,118.19 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Chandigarh: Eight freehold residential sites to be auctioned in March
news.para: The eight sites are in sectors 33, 34, 35, 37 and 40. Sector has 40 three sites, Sector 37 two and the remaining sectors one each. The area varies between 250 square yards and 527 square yards.

news.title: Calcutta HC chief justice nominates senior judge for RERA implementation in West Bengal
news.para: The counsel for the state government has informed the Supreme Court about this development while appealing to the top court to not entertain a recent application filed by the Forum for People’s Collective Efforts (FPCE), a pan-India homebuyers’ body that is aiming to push the implementation of RERA in the state.
